Azure External Identities allow organizations to securely collaborate with users outside their organization.

This includes:

* Partners
* Vendors
* Customers

External users can use their own identities while accessing resources securely.

For example, a company can collaborate with external consultants.

# Real-Life Use Case:
A real-life use case is B2B partnerships.

# Real-Life Example:
Another example is customer portals.

External identities expand secure collaboration beyond organizational boundaries.
